    <h2>What each one actually is</h2>

    <h3>Nexrial — full CTMS for independent research sites</h3>
    <p>
      Nexrial is a site-operations CTMS for independent research sites and small site
      networks running 5–25 concurrent studies. Verified native capabilities include:
      subject tracking with visit scheduling, delegation log with PI e-signature and
      PDF export, monitoring visit management (findings, action items), IRB submission
      tracking, protocol deviation logging, SOP management with version gating, training
      log with expiry tracking, consent version tracking, invoice management, and a
      21 CFR Part 11 immutable audit trail enforced by three independent database-level
      defenses.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pricing is published: <strong>$299/month Core, $599/month Pro</strong>, plus a
      Founding Site Program — 50% off for life for the first 3–5 sites ($149 Core / $299 Pro).
      No sales call required to evaluate cost.
    </p>

    <h3>Florence Healthcare — site enablement platform (eISF, eTMF, eConsent)</h3>
    <p>
      Florence Healthcare is a document and workflow platform for clinical trials,
      not a full CTMS. Its core products are:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>eBinders (eISF)</strong> — electronic Investigator Site File and
        participant binder. Handles regulatory document organization, version control,
        role-based access, audit trails, Part 11 / Annex 11 e-signatures on regulatory
        documents, and long-term archiving. Integrates with CTMS and EMR/EHR systems.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>SiteLink</strong> — document exchange and remote monitoring access for
        sponsors and CROs. Enables sponsors to review site documents digitally before
        on-site visits without duplicate uploads.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>eTMF</strong> — Electronic Trial Master File for sponsors managing
        regulatory documentation centrally across multiple sites.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>eConsent</strong> — digitizes informed consent workflows for research
        participants and site staff.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Florence reports serving 65,000 study sites across 90+ countries with 600+
      sponsors supported. It is well-regarded for its eISF implementation — if your
      primary need is a deeply capable, widely adopted eISF with sponsor remote access,
      Florence eBinders is a legitimate option.
    </p>
    <p>
      Florence pricing is not publicly listed. Contact Florence Healthcare at
      <a href="https://florencehc.com" rel="noopener">florencehc.com</a> for a quote.
      <!-- Sources: florencehc.com, florencehc.com/products, florencehc.com/ebinders — fetched 2026-04-23 -->
    </p>
