    <div class="doc-block">
    <h2>FAQ</h2>

    <h3>Does Florence Healthcare replace a CTMS?</h3>
    <p>
      No. Florence Healthcare replaces paper site files and adds sponsor remote monitoring
      access — it is an eISF, eTMF, and eConsent platform. It does not cover visit
      scheduling, monitoring visit management (findings, action items), protocol deviation
      tracking, IRB submission tracking, SOP management, or invoice management. Sites
      that use Florence typically still need a CTMS alongside it.
    </p>

    <h3>Does Nexrial implement 21 CFR Part 11 controls?</h3>
    <p>
      Nexrial is designed against the controls of 21 CFR Part 11 Subpart B (electronic
      records). Audit-log integrity is enforced by three independent database-level
      defenses: UPDATE, DELETE, and TRUNCATE are revoked at the database user level,
      ensuring audit records cannot be modified even by application code. A full
      validation package (VAL-PLAN, IQ/OQ/PQ, VAL-REPORT) with executed-run evidence
      is available under NDA. Part 11 is a design standard, not a certification — see
      <a href="https://nexrial.com/trust">nexrial.com/trust</a> for the current control posture.
    </p>

    <h3>Does Florence eBinders have a Part 11 e-signature?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes. Florence eBinders supports Part 11 and Annex 11 compliant e-signatures on
      regulatory documents within the eISF — covering document sign-offs in the
      Investigator Site File. Nexrial's native e-signature covers delegation log
      PI sign-off and enrollment authorization. These are different use cases:
      Florence signs regulatory documents; Nexrial signs operational records.
    </p>

    <h3>My sponsor uses Florence SiteLink — do I have to use eBinders?</h3>
    <p>
      If your sponsor conducts remote monitoring visits through Florence SiteLink, they
      may require you to have Florence eBinders set up so they can access your site
      documents remotely. This is a sponsor-driven requirement, not a regulatory
      mandate. Check with your monitor whether SiteLink connectivity is required before
      evaluating your eISF options.
    </p>
